re and Operations on projects and define strategy in the transformation of existing infrastructure and network solutions to the cloud environment. ? We\u2019re looking for a strong candidate who is sharp, adaptable and agile enough to resolve problems, proactively think about solutions and get \"hands-on\" when needed; who can context switch between the day to day running of the Infrastructure and Network operation and long term strategic thinking setting our infrastructure and network services up for long term success ? You must have the ability to think strategically, demonstrating an in-depth understanding of current and future trends in the IT market with a sound knowledge and experience of outsourcing, partner management, licencing and commercials across strategic partners such as Accenture, Microsoft and Oracle. ? They should also be able to lead a highly motivated, technically capable and flexible team with the ability to build very strong relationships with key stakeholders both internally and externally and demonstrate an ability to influence partners to deliver the best results for the Group. ? They must be a passionate advocate for the services and systems to the business, IT, and all Service Providers, someone who is able to hold their own and challenge in a technical discussion and is accountable for service and system performance across the enterprise including the identification and execution of specific improvement programs, removal of risk and definition of the system and service strategy. ? Main Responsibilities: Lead the design, implementation and delivery of a NextGen infrastructure and network strategy Provide a world class customer centric support for customers, driving a strong positive value proposition and perception of our infrastructure and network services Manage senior stakeholders and keeping them informed and supported at all times Represent the Infrastructure and Network Services teams at various meetings, i.e. Change Advisory Board, Monthly Service Reviews and Quarterly Business Reviews Manage day to day operations to improve infrastructure and network costs, performance and end user satisfaction Measure and improve your services and team through CSFs, KPIs and purpose driven metrics Achieve quarterly objectives in line with the Tech strategy (and therefore the overall business strategy) Act as the escalation point for all issues regarding customer support for infrastructure and network services Deliver continuous improvements in areas of infrastructure and network services provision Provide leadership in planning and managing infrastructure operations and production support, systems and database administration and network operations Manage and maintain all infrastructure and network assets, building an end to end asset management capability to ensure the full lifetime cycle value of our assets are achieved and all assets are managed from inception through to decommissioning and disposal Manage strategic relationships with key product and service providers, working in close collaboration with third party service providers to provide an infrastructure that surpasses our customers\u2019 expectations to access and use their business applications Maintain, challenge and report on SLAs with third party providers Interface with stakeholders to define infrastructure support initiatives and solutions for improving service efficiency and effectiveness, undertake effective stakeholder engagement and management at all times Analyse and predict trends and develop long range plans designed to maintain cost effectiveness Develop reporting for all services provided in areas that include quality, capacity, systems and responsiveness/availability Ensure the infrastructure and network team is mitigating, monitoring and managing infrastructure related risks Work closely with project managers for time allocation and prioritisation as well as delivery of our portfolio pipeline Fully accountable and responsible for managing the infrastructure and network CAPEX and OPEX budgets, as well as setting future budget forecasts for the infrastructure and network services Work closely with our internal partners (such as Finance, Procurement and Legal) to ensure your services are in line with the wider Chalhoub Group shared services framework Fully accountable and responsible for all aspects of Security Operations (SecOps) across all endpoints on the infrastructure and network Occasional travel to various sites required within the UAE region ? Experience, Skills & Knowledge 7 + years\u2019 experience in Cloud Services including Microsoft / Oracle / Google and Amazon 10 + years of experience in IT infrastructure operations with 5+ years leadership; with in-depth experience of managing teams responsible for architecture design and deployment, systems lifecycle management and infrastructure planning and operations Holds Industry Accredited Qualifications i.e. MSCE: Core Infrastructure, CCNA, CNIT or CNIDP ?ITIL Foundation Certification v3 (minimum) Excellent understanding of Devops / Agile methodology; with in-depth experience of working in both traditional IT and DevOps environments Excellent understanding of Microsoft / Oracle licencing and maintenance plans Ability to think out of the box and come up with ideas to enhance processes, systems; demonstrate strong analytical and problem-solving skills Excellent communication / presentation skills Strong organisation skills and conscientious attention to detail Strategic thinker focused on technology trends with excellent stakeholder management skills Excellent understanding of Enterprise Infrastructure, both on-premise and cloud based including network technologies with a thorough understanding of Data Centre environments and Cloud computing technology Proven track record of customer satisfaction with a strong focus on results, continuous track record of successfully delivering enterprise wide infrastructure and network services simultaneously Possesses a growth mindset in the areas of people, process, product and partners; to drive for a step change in proactive customer centric service across our infrastructure and network estate Experience in supporting Microsoft software and server systems including Office365 / Active Directory Virtualisation (VMWare / Citrix), CI/CD automation; ARM templating Monitoring & Alerting technologies such as APM, Nagios, Grafana, New Relic MDM (Mobile Device Management) solutions Experience in areas such as network design and administration, data center operations, database administration, and systems programming and administration Strong knowledge and understanding of business needs with ability to establish and maintain a high level of customer trust and confidence Experience in automated infrastructure services management Strong understanding of new and emerging technologies Proven experience of successfully managing teams and setting them up for success including goal setting and performance management Ready to join our exciting transformation to become a hybrid retailer, bringing luxury experiences to the fingertips of our customers everywhere? Now\u2019s your chance. By being part of our journey here at Chalhoub Group, you can make a real impact on customers and some of the finest brands in the world. In return, you\u2019ll have everything you need to innovate your career. ? What we can offer you We will help shape your journey with us through enriching experiences, learning and development opportunities and exposure to different assignments within your role or through internal mobility. Our Group offers the opportunity to support careers that may span different teams, different job roles, different categories and even different countries.?We offer diverse career paths for those who show drive and passion as well as the desire to learn and grow. Amazing benefits We recognise the value that you bring, and we strive to provide a competitive benefits package which in